The paper deals with the analysis of a formal model of sensor networks, which involves computation and interaction between identical mobile devices. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. However, the focus on consensus and expected termination time suggests that the paper is more likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Theory (cs.IT), Networked Systems (cs.NI), or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.DS and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories, as the former deals with the analysis of algorithms and data structures, while the latter deals with the study of social and information networks.
